06/04/2011
BERLIN, Germany -- Police in Dusseldorf have arrested a Serb convicted in Croatia of war crimes committed during the 1991-1995 war, according to a statement Tuesday (April 5th). Renato Petrov, a former policeman in the self-declared Serbian Autonomous Region of Krajina, was sentenced in absentia by Croatia in 1995 to 20 years in prison for taking part in the 1991 killings of 43 Croatian soldiers and civilians in Zadar. (Vjesnik, Vecernji List, Tanjug, Nova TV - 05/04/11)
